text:
Santa Clara County has only 50 empty ICU beds after setting a new record with 1,450 new coronavirus infections. 62 coronavirus patients were hospitalized on Sunday alone.

text:

name: sfchronicle
text:
Green Valley Ranch, a 950-acre property with three lakes in Napa County that was purchased in 1978 for $850,000 by a group of young men and used communally for decades, was sold Monday to an unidentified buyer for $15.7 million in cash.
